# Add Puter.js Seedream Provider (Free, No API Key)

## Background

The current "Seedream" image provider in OpenMAIC calls the **ByteDance Ark API** (`ark.cn-beijing.volces.com`) using the server-side route `/api/generate/image`, which requires a paid Volcengine API key.

**Puter.js** offers a completely **free, unlimited**, client-side API for the same Seedream models (`ByteDance-Seed/Seedream-4.0` and `ByteDance-Seed/Seedream-3.0`) via `puter.ai.txt2img()`. No API keys or backend required â€” it loads a script tag and all generation runs in the browser under a "User-Pays" model (each Puter user has their own quota).

This plan adds a new `puter-seedream` provider that runs 100% on the client side via the Puter.js SDK, bypassing the existing server-side image generation pipeline entirely.

---

## How Puter.js Works

```html
<!-- Just add this script tag â€” no config, no API keys -->
<script src="https://js.puter.com/v2/"></script>
```

```js
// Generate an image (returns an <img> HTMLElement)
puter.ai.txt2img(
  "A futuristic cityscape",
  {
    model: "ByteDance-Seed/Seedream-4.0",
    provider: "together-ai",
    disable_safety_checker: true,
    width: 960,
    height: 960
  }
).then(imageElement => {
  // imageElement is a ready <img> with .src set
  document.body.appendChild(imageElement);
});
```

The returned `<img>` element has its `.src` pointing to a blob/object URL of the generated image.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Client-side only**: Puter.js runs entirely in the browser. There's no server route involved â€” the image is generated on the client. This means:
> - No API key is needed â€” users use their own Puter account quota (free tier included).
> - It cannot be used server-side (e.g., in `classroom-generation.ts`), and that's fine because the existing classroom image generation already happens client-side via `media-orchestrator.ts`.

> [!WARNING]
> **Puter.js login requirement**: Puter.js may prompt the user to log in to puter.com on first use. This is expected behavior for the "User-Pays" model. We should document this in the UI.

> [!NOTE]
> The existing `seedream` provider (Volcengine/Ark API) is **NOT removed**. We add `puter-seedream` as a new parallel option so users can choose either.

